Gunmen have attacked security operatives and set ablaze a Customs van along Issele-Azagba Road, in the Aniocha North Local Government Area of Delta State. PUNCH Metro gathered that the hoodlums ambushed the team, made up of the police and vigilantes, at a Customs checkpoint. “There were heavy gunshots along Issele-Azagba on Wednesday evening by unknown gunmen. “They attacked security men along the highway and shot discriminately. In the process, they set ablaze a Customs van,” a witness, who did not want to be identified, said. The state Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Edafe Bright, on Thursday, confirmed the attack, adding that nobody was killed. He said, “The armed robbers shot at the vigilantes, but they quickly took cover; no death was recorded.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com